  "prompt": "What are the best coffee shops with Wi-Fi in San Francisco for evening work?",
  "response": "Here are some great coffee shops in San Francisco that offer Wi-Fi and a conducive atmosphere for evening work:\n\n1. **Blue Bottle Coffee** - Known for its high-quality brews, Blue Bottle has several locations in San Francisco. Most of them have ample seating and a relaxed vibe, making it a good spot for working in the evening.\n\n2. **Philz Coffee** - With locations throughout the city, Philz offers a unique coffee experience and a comfortable working environment. Many locations have ample seating, and the laid-back atmosphere can be perfect for evening productivity.\n\n3. **Stumptown Coffee Roasters** - Located in the Ace Hotel, Stumptown has a modern ambiance and good Wi-Fi. It's an excellent spot for those who need a quiet environment to focus in the evenings.\n\n4. **Ritual Coffee Roasters** - This local favorite is known for its strong coffee and inviting space. The atmosphere is suitable for evening work, especially at their Mission location.\n\n5. **Tartine Bakery** - Famous for its pastries, Tartine Bakery also serves coffee and has a cozy setting that's great for working. Be aware that it can get busy, but the vibe is usually conducive to focus.\n\n6. **Equator Coffees** - This coffee shop has various locations, including one in the Marina District. They offer excellent coffee and a comfortable setting with a good environment for working.\n\n7. **Cafe Trieste** - Located in North Beach, this iconic caf\u00e9 has a rich history and a lively atmosphere. It offers Wi-Fi and a great place to work in the evening while enjoying live music.\n\n8. **Coffee Bar** - With a couple of locations in the city, Coffee Bar is known for its friendly atmosphere and good Wi-Fi, making it a nice spot for working in the evenings.\n\n9. **Mazarine Coffee** - Located on Geary Street, Mazarine Coffee offers a pleasant ambiance with ample seating and strong Wi-Fi, ideal for evening work sessions.\n\n10. **The Mill** - A hybrid coffee shop and bakery, The Mill features a spacious area with communal tables that can be great for evening work. Their toast and coffee are highly praised.\n\nAlways check with individual locations for their hours and Wi-Fi availability, as it can vary. Enjoy your coffee and work!",
